main event: A round, white and green object was observed in Detroit, Michigan on January 23, 1935.
interesting points: The object was described as the size of a Lost Ro motor station,It was concluded that the sighting was likely a balloon but other possibilities included military aircraft or astronomical phenomena,The observer used binoculars to assist in the observation,The object was stationary and did not disappear during the sighting,The sighting lasted for one hour.
witness description: Civilian, identified as Mrs. Detroit Michigan
